description.0: Can the Jedi Knights protect Coruscant from the Sith and the Mandalores?
description.1: Tycho Celchu must make the hardest decision of his lifetime: choosing between saving his friends and supporting his cause. Disguised as an Imperial fighter pilot, Rogue Squadron flyer Tycho Celchu has successfully infiltrated the Imperial troops. But success turns sour when his TIE fighter unit encounters Wedge Antilles and Rogue Squadron! If he abandons his post with the Imperial fighters, he abandons the cause of the New Republic; but if he stands his ground, he risks killing his comrades. Either way this Rebel plays, he plays a losing game . . .
description.7: Doc has the rareified opportunity to meet the leader of the Coven…before he decides to destroy it.
description.8: The tyranny has ended. But what will take its place? It is now five years after'Return of the Jedi.'Leia'and'Han'are married and have shouldered heavy burdens in the government of the'New Republic. And'Luke Skywalker'is the first in a hoped-for new line of'Jedi Knights. But thousands of light-years away, the last of the Emperor's warlords, Grand Admiral Thrawn, has taken command of the remains of the Imperial fleet. Thrawn has made two vital discoveries that could destroy the Rebel Alliance's New Republic. The tale that emerges is a towering epic of action, invention, mystery, and a spectacle of galactic scale- in short, a story that is worthy of the name Star Wars.
description.14: Those infected with the Skrull virus continue to struggle with their less-than-human identity. Captain America joins the Kill Krew, giving this ragtag band the back-up of a seasoned Avenger!
description.15: While Peter and MJ get to the bottom of his nightmares, Doc Ock discovers that Seward has created a bridge between a virtual reality and the real world! Can Ben stop the 8-armed woman before it's too late?
description.16: After filing for bankruptcy, Wasp discovers that Tony Stark may be behind her financial ruin. Vision makes a horrifying discovery involving two residents of Avengers Mansion. Giant-Man collects all evidence and concludes that Kang has returned!
description.24: While trying to save Pete, Kitty discovers Black Air has alien creatures ready for battle!
description.25: In the aftermath of "OVER THE EDGE", one of Marvel's most enduring characters made the ultimate sacrifice. Now, Marvel's best and brightest pay their last respects to Nick Fury, agent of S.H.I.E.L.D. and the greatest spy who ever lived.
description.27: The tentacled menace revealed! Plus, a shocking development in Mary Jane's pregnancy will leave Peter with his hands full...and the most difficult decision of his life!
description.29: While weak and dying, Thor discovers Yggdrasil is in danger and uses his remaining strength to stop further damage to the tree! Meanwhile, Amora is formulating a plan of her own.
description.30: Peter Parker shows tremendous personal growth when he gains sympathy for a school bully that is emotionally abused at home. Spidey's exploring what it truly takes to be a super hero!
description.31: Sworn ally becomes lethal enemy, as the New Warriors and Scarlet Spider subdue a hypnotized Peter Parker...who's still trying to kill MJ under the Jackal's influence!
description.33: Ben Grimm returns to his human skin, but scars still remain from his time as Thing. Namor puts the moves on Sue Richards, (again). In battle against the Tomorrow Man, Ant-Man finds himself facing villains of the future...and the past! Iron Man 2020 duking it out alongside Two-Gun Kid!
description.34: Marrow, the leader of the Gene Nation, has tagged innocent civilians with explosives that can go off at any minute. The only way to deactivate the devices is to stop Marrow's heart. As the former leader of the Morlocks, Storm steps up to take Marrow down.
description.35: The Dark Riders have freed Cyber and prepare him for the Clan Akkaba. Wolverine agrees to a training session with Generation X- but will he be able to wrangle in these powerful teenage mutants? Jubilee and Wolverine reunited at last!
description.39: The Starjammers must escape Shi'ar military forces and relocate Kree captives in their debut issue!
description.42: Some believe heroism is a result of genetics; others, that it is a result of teaching. But for'Artoo, it's the result of a computer virus! Following their fateful encounter with'Boonda'the'Hutt,'Threepio'and Artoo are acquired by an'Ithorian'on'Nar Shaddaa. When the Ithorian's herd ship is attacked by alien kidnappers, Artoo is compelled to protect an apparently helpless human. Artoo's selfless act is soon revealed to exceed standard droid programming when Threepio discovers that his small friend has been overtaken by the'Caretaker virus!
description.43: Tycho Celchu has infiltrated the Imperial Forces. Now he can communicate vital strategic information that will give the Rebellion an upper hand! But when he's pressed to lead a raid on his old Rogue Squadron teammates, he must choose between saving his comrades and serving the cause.
description.44: Leia has uncovered Ranulf as an Imperial spy! She and her covert Rebel team are holding him prisoner and preparing his execution, but when the Empire has the Rebel Mora in its merciless grasp, it's Ranulf who volunteers to rush to her rescue! Is it a plot to regain his freedom, or can an Imperial officer repeal the indoctrination of the Empire?
description.45: Can Exar Kun and Ulic Qel-Droma bring backa new Sith Golden Age?
description.47: What if Legion had killed Magneto? The X-Men fail to hold Legion back from traveling to the past to kill Erik Lensherr, with dire consequences for the Marvel Universe- most of all Legion himself!
description.48: None other than Nick Fury requests Strange's help in order to find one of the most intimidating heroes ever known…any guesses?
description.49: Thor heads to Eric Masterson's grave where he finds Carl 'The Crusher' Creel waiting for him! Is the Absorbing Man at the gravesite for all the wrong reasons?
description.54: Ben's Vermont getaway is cut short when Seward Trainer contacts him with an urgent call! Meanwhile, Peter Parker is tormented by a vivid nightmare he has no recollection of!
description.55: The Avengers attempt to unwind with a summer BBQ, but inevitably, things go awry. Hercules arrives on the scene with a young fortune-teller claiming to be the future son of Crystal and Quicksilver. Meanwhile, Wasp receives shocking news about her bank statement.
description.56: Captain America has learned that he has 24 hours left to live... So how should he spend it?
description.58: The New Warriors are targeted for their 'unique genetics'. The 'gene-cleansing' Eugenix have deemed each member unfit to live...and are now trying to eliminate the team!
description.61: A mysterious new evil has attacked Force Works, and only US Agent and Century remain standing to save them! But can they even trust one another?
description.62: Black Bolt goes berserk! Who can stop him and what part will the Inhuman Royal Family play?
description.68: Disgraced journalist Eddie Brock is reborn as the Lethal Protector-Venom! Adapting Spider-Man's ""Alien Suit Saga!""
description.71: Pete Wisdom is captured by Black Air! Can Shadowcat find him on her own?
description.72: Hulk on the hunt! The Jade Giant is searching for a drug dealer with intel regarding Abomination, which means it's time for an investigation in the underbelly of New York City. But that turf already belongs to another crime-fighter - Frank Castle, better known as the Punisher!
description.73: Tony Stark experiences a blackout and wonders if he is having a full-on meltdown.
description.74: A visit by Ben Reilly to his former mentor, Seward Trainer, turns into a deathtrap for the Scarlet Spider as he goes up against a mysterious new foe.'
description.75: The First Appearance of Venom 2099!  Who is Venom 2099 and why is he dead set on murdering Miguel O'Hara and Tyler Stone?
description.76: Peter Parker's teen years are spotlighted in this series, from his job at the Daily Bugle, to the Ol' Parker Luck always landing him in trouble. In this debut issue, Spider-Man reflects back on his life, and how it's evolved since donning super hero threads.
description.77: Black Cat guest-stars! Ben Reilly and Peter Parker must reach a decision- who will take on the mantle of Spider-Man?
description.79: The Fantastic Four, transformed into...Things! The entire crew does battle as ever lovin' Things, and Ben Grimm can't seem to convince his teammates of their true identities. Who is Mico Rodolfo, the hunter behind this strange metamorphosis? Namor demands an audience with the Invisible Woman, as only Namor can.
description.80: In New York City, Wolverine, Storm, Cannonball, and Detective Charlotte Jones must contend with the Gene Nation!
description.81: Beginning to slip into his old self, Wolverine goes out for a beer with New Mutant Cannonball. But a round of brews turns into a battle...against the Unstoppable Juggernaut! Cyber gets an early release from Muir Island.
description.85: Sunspot battles Mimic- despite Cable's orders! Will Mimic's powers overload Sunspot and destroy him for good? Meanwhile, Siryn is trapped in a hospital for the clinically insane and she's desperate for help…desperate enough to call Deadpool?
description.87: Kill Krew member Ryder makes the best of a bad situation, as he recruits others who have been infected with the body-morphing Skrull virus. But with a shortened life expectancy, will these new Kill Krew members be able to stamp out the Skrulls before they infiltrate society?
description.89: The Mandalorians are recruited by the Sith, which leads to an all-out attack on Coruscant.
description.91: FINAL ISSUE! The Infinity Gems have vanished, leaving behind an emptiness and a devastating question…what does this mean for the Infinity Watch? Are their days as a team finally over?
description.92: Doctor Strange finally has a new look… the one you know and love!
description.97: When Rogue Squadron leader Wedge Antilles is downed in a bloody battle against Imperial All Terrain Scout Transports, he is forced to form an uneasy alliance with the Cilpari natives, whose dislike for the Rebels is only dwarfed by their hatred for the Empire. Wedge must regroup Rogue Squadron before the Cilpari alliance is shattered, and rejoin the battle to save the galaxy!
description.98: Jabba'has got a hot'freighter'on his'hands'and he's looking to unload it, quickly and discreetly. Enter'Cabrool Nuum, a second-hand'ship'trader whose reputation for discretion is as long as his many years in the business. Unfortunately for Jabba, the years seem to have caught up with Cabrool, and his murderous offspring have taken advantage of the old man's dotage, just as they plan to take advantage of Jabba's impending arrival! In a seedy corner of'the galaxy, on a planet of back-stabbing opportunists, Jabba the'Hutt'is about to land face first in'the Dynasty Trap!
description.99: It's the Battle of Tandankin and the Rogue Squadron aim to win!

2.text: Cassidy Keep has disappeared! When Synch and Chamber get sucked into the same dimension as Banshee's home, it's up to the rest of Generation X to bring them back.

3.text: Domino takes on Grizzly! But can she bring herself to fight a long-time friend? Then Cable makes a major decision - to return to his future timeline!

4.text: Terrorists have holed up inside the Lincoln Memorial. Their demands don't include getaways or money-they simply want Captain America. And if their demands aren't met, they'll blow themselves up, along with everyone inside the memorial!

5.text: Is this the end of the line for Peter Parker? Ben Reilly becomes the only active Spider-Man!

6.text: The X-Men recruit a young man named Chris Bradley who has recently developed mutant powers. After training alongside and befriending the X-Men, Chris discovers that he has the Legacy Virus, a terminal illness that effects mutants.

7.text: Doc has the rareified opportunity to meet the leader of the Coven…before he decides to destroy it.

10.text: Carnage achieves terrifying power, while Venom brings the entire symbiote race to the brink of extinction.

11.text: All is not as it seems at the Weisman Institute for the Criminally Insane, as Deadpool and Siryn can attest! X-Force is scattered left and right, as confusing leads lead to more dead ends. Who is Jeremy Stevens? What are his plans for X-Force’s heaviest hitters?

12.text: Dark Beast makes a timely rescue when Nate comes to blows with Rex aboard a ship.

17.text: Doctor Doom remains isolated at the top, crippled and cut off from former alliances and favors. John Herod presents an alternative ‘puppet’ to rule America – Captain America 2099!

18.text: After their last adventure in space, the X-Men just want some rest and relaxation, but trouble from the Savage Land finds its way to New York City and only the X-Men can stop it!

19.text: Nearly burnt-to-a-crisp Venom decides that due justice is coming for the Sin-Eater! Enter Anne Weying as SHE-VENOM!

20.text: Spider-Woman and Moonraker welcome the Scarlet Witch and the U.S. Agent from New York, but a series of unexplained time rifts complicates things.

21.text: While on assignment for the Daily Bugle, Ben Urich's nephew Phil stumbles upon the Green Goblin's old lair.

22.text: Wolverine and Gambit have been saved by an enigmatic woman and the trio has made their way into the London sewers. Who is this woman? Can she be trusted? Is she even human?

23.text: An old suit is put to use again when Daredevil’s past starts to haunt him!

28.text: Venom 2099! Which strange assailant has bonded with the symbiote, and what do they want with Tyler Stone? Plus, Miguel gets a promotion at Alchemax.

36.text: Rogue decides she needs a break from her relationship with Gambit and the X-Men at large.

38.text: Ben and Janine finally decide to be together. But their happiness is soon interrupted by the rogue clone called Kaine!

40.text: An untold tale from the classic Spidey series in honor of the wallcrawler's 50th Anniversary!

46.text: Cable goes to Professor X with an important request - help Nathan track down his wayward son, Tyler Summers! Plus, a murder investigation brings Domino face to face with an old friend!

47.text: What if Legion had killed Magneto? The X-Men fail to hold Legion back from traveling to the past to kill Erik Lensherr, with dire consequences for the Marvel Universe- most of all Legion himself!

48.text: None other than Nick Fury requests Strange's help in order to find one of the most intimidating heroes ever known…any guesses?

50.text: Banshee is haunted by nightmares from his time as an Interpol agent, and Emma Frost is listening in!  Meanwhile, The Gen X kids try to cope with each other and the new additions Artie and Leech.

53.text: Gambit heads to London to see if the sparks will still fly with some love interests from the past. Upon his arrival he discovers that the women he came for are all being murdered. The prime suspect: Wolverine!

57.text: While prowling the campus grounds, Wolverine notices something amiss. An interdimensional portal emerges at Xavier Institute! Wolverine is joined by fellow X-Man Nightcrawler, as the two thwart an invasion by N’Garai aliens. When robbed of his humanity, will Wolverine once again fall to berserker rage? Plus, Maverick crash lands at the Institute with some shadowy dirt on Weapon X…and it involves none other than Deadpool!

59.text: Carnage begins his quest for symbiotes, while Ben, Peter and Eddie Brock stave off the villain's attacks!

60.text: Ben Reilly crosses paths with the Vulture!

61.text: A mysterious new evil has attacked Force Works, and only US Agent and Century remain standing to save them! But can they even trust one another?

63.text: Eddie Brock's ex-wife is the next target of the Sin-Eater! Will a symbiote slugfest ensue?

64.text: And so it begins! The Crossing saga that will rock the Marvel Universe and take Earth's Mightiest Heroes to the edge...and beyond! However the story opens with a celebration at Avengers Mansion! It's the anniversary of the team's founding many years ago! And this gathering of old friends provides an opportunity to rekindle past romances (between the Vision and the Scarlet Witch) and also past animosities (between Hawkeye and Iron Man)! Right before Jarvis serves the special anniversary dinner, a strange group of beings attacks the mansion! The Avengers quickly assemble outside and repel the invaders! But left behind from the attack is the former avenger Gilgamesh...in an aged and dying state! What happened to the forgotten eternal? And who is the mysterious girl slipping in and out of the timestream? The frightening answers are coming in the days ahead! And the Avengers will never be the same again!

65.text: Have the men and women we know as heroes made the global radioactive situation better or worse? Here's a hint: In the Ruins, radiation only kills.

66.text: Both Kaine and Ben begin romantic relationships, with disastrously different results!

67.text: Alchemax and John Herod collaborate to deliver America from the despotic hands of Doom. Enter Captain America 2099!

69.text: Jean will do anything to stop D'Ken, even make the ultimate sacrifice!

70.text: As Daredevil self-reflects on his new love of violence, he questions who he is.  Meanwhile, the Punisher teaches Nick Fury a lesson.

75.text: After last issue’s shocker, Tyler Stone is lying at death’s door! And Miguel’s mother Conchata is to blame! Spider-Man’s side hustle for President Doom hits a snag…

82.text: The X-Men and Acolytes crash-land back to Earth’s surface only to be confronted by an even larger calamity.

83.text: Peter is overcome with the urge to kill Mary Jane!

85.text: Sunspot battles Mimic- despite Cable's orders! Will Mimic's powers overload Sunspot and destroy him for good? Meanwhile, Siryn is trapped in a hospital for the clinically insane and she's desperate for help…desperate enough to call Deadpool?

86.text: The lady's name is…SELENE! Nate and Maddie arrive in Paris, but cannot comprehend the full extent of Selene's manipulation.

88.text: The Jackal's personal dossier on the clones of Clone Saga!

91.text: FINAL ISSUE! The Infinity Gems have vanished, leaving behind an emptiness and a devastating question…what does this mean for the Infinity Watch? Are their days as a team finally over?

92.text: Doctor Strange finally has a new look… the one you know and love!

93.text: Emma Frost and Generation X combat the substantial new threat that is Gene Nation.  Elsewhere, Chamber comforts Husk in a time of need, and the two grow closer.

95.text: An old friend of Professor X flees Genosha to bring him dire news, but Genoshan magistrates Pipeline and Hawkshaw attempt to bring her back, no matter the cost! Can Cable and X-Force fight them off and learn her dark secret?
